text.0: In March of 2020, a sailor on the U.S.S. Theodore Roosevelt was identified as having #SARSCoV2 infection. Over the following weeks, 1271 crew members positive, the majority were asymptomatic at time of lab diagnosis. 23 crew members were hospitalized, and 1 died. #COVID19
text.1: U.S. Marine Corps recruits quarantined at home for 2 weeks; after this period, 0.9% were found to be infected with severe acute #SARSCoV2. During a second, supervised 2-week quarantine on a college campus, 1.9% had become newly infected, and most were asymptomatic. #COVID19
